%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20cofounder%20of%20Wiz%2C%20Google's%20%2432%20billion%20acquisition%20target%2C%20says%20vibe%20coding%20must%20be%20met%20with%20'vibe%20security'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222021%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20Israeli%20man%20with%20cropped%20brown%20hair%20and%20a%20black%20T-shirt.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6889028985e81483682edb46%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221516%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWiz%20cofounder%20and%20chief%20technology%20officer%20Ami%20Luttwak.%3Cp%3EWiz%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EGoogle's%20%2432%20billion%20bid%20to%20buy%20Wiz%20challenges%20the%20notion%20of%20a%20mega-deal%20drought%20in%20tech.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAmi%20Luttwak%20helped%20build%20Wiz%20through%20a%20pandemic%20and%20a%20new%20tech%20paradigm.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20tells%20Business%20Insider%20why%20the%20rise%20of%20AI%20demands%20new%20security%20approaches.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20Google%20agreed%20to%20buy%20Israeli-American%20cloud%20security%20firm%20Wiz%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20making%20for%20the%20search%20giant's%20largest%20acquisition%2C%20it%20threw%20a%20%2432%20billion%20bucket%20of%20water%20on%20the%20idea%20that%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftech-merger-deals-harder-adobe-figma-antitrust-startups-exit-options-2023-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emega-deal%3C%2Fa%3E%20drought%20was%20here%20to%20stay.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20March%2C%20Google%20agreed%20to%20acquire%20the%20five-year-old%20startup%20at%20an%20all-cash%20price%20roughly%20equal%20to%20Iceland's%20gross%20domestic%20product%20last%20year%2C%20pending%20regulatory%20sign-off.%20The%20acquisition%20now%20stands%20as%20an%20early%20litmus%20test%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-wiz-acquisition-trump-ipo-big-tech-startups-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ETrump%3C%2Fa%3E%20administration's%20willingness%20to%20green-light%20pricey%20Big%20Tech%20mergers%20and%20acquisitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20Wiz%20cofounder%20and%20chief%20technology%20officer%20Ami%20Luttwak%2C%20the%20moment%20feels%20like%20d%C3%A9j%C3%A0%E2%80%91vu%E2%80%94%20the%20same%20founding%20team%20sold%20its%20last%20outfit%2C%20Adallom%2C%20to%20Microsoft%20in%202015.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFounded%20in%20March%20of%202020%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwiz-cloud-security-ai-boom-ipo-google-takeover-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EWiz%3C%2Fa%3E%20crash-landed%20in%20a%20pandemic%20that%20yanked%20workloads%20out%20of%20on-prem%20server%20racks%20and%20thrust%20them%20into%20the%20cloud%20almost%20overnight.%20The%20crew%20pivoted%20from%20network%20exposure%20to%20cloud%20security%20and%20says%20that%20within%2018%20months%2C%20it%20was%20posting%20%24100%20million%20in%20annual%20recurring%20revenue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%20the%20company%20finds%20itself%20riding%20an%20even%20wilder%20wave.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20ability%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-code-meta-microsoft-google-llamacon-engineers-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ewrite%20code%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20turned%20every%20developer%20into%20a%20feature%20factory.%20However%2C%20Luttwak%20says%20the%20proliferation%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-hackers-models-hugging-face-opensource-jfrog-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Enew%20attack%20surfaces%3C%2Fa%3E%20leaves%20most%20security%20teams%20overwhelmed%20and%20outnumbered.%20Luttwak's%20answer%3F%20If%20builders%20can%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvibe-coding-ai-silicon-valley-andrej-karpathy-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Evibe-code%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20an%20app%20in%20an%20hour%2C%20security%20has%20to%20vibe%20right%20alongside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20at%20Business%20Insider's%20headquarters%20in%20New%20York%20City%2C%20we%20asked%20Luttwak%20about%20building%20a%20company%20through%20a%20pandemic%2C%20a%20new%20tech%20paradigm%2C%20and%20making%20cloud%20security%20part%20of%20an%20engineer's%20workflow.%20He%20declined%20to%20answer%20any%20questions%20about%20Google's%20planned%20acquisition.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20Q%26amp%3BA%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20clarity%20and%20length.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThis%20is%20pretty%20much%20the%20same%20team%20between%20your%20first%20startup%20and%20Wiz%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20the%20same%20team%2C%20basically.%20The%20team%20is%20what%20makes%20the%20company%20and%20defines%20how%20it%20operates.%20It's%20not%20the%20specific%20direction%20or%20idea.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20left%20Microsoft%2C%20we%20didn't%20know%20what%20we%20wanted%20to%20build.%20We%20just%20said%2C%20'We%20have%20a%20chance%20to%20get%20back%20together%2C%20so%20let's%20do%20it.'%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20started%20out%20with%20another%20service%2C%20right%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20started%20in%20networking%2C%20then%20COVID%20hit%2C%20and%20no%20one%20wanted%20to%20talk%20about%20a%20future%20network%20architecture.%20It%20was%20all%20about%2C%20'How%20can%20you%20help%20me%20now%3F'%3Cem%3E%20%3C%2Fem%3EWe%20had%20to%20pivot%2C%20but%20we%20like%20to%20pivot.%20That's%20the%20fun%20of%20startups%20%E2%80%94%20to%20find%20real%20problems%2C%20not%20the%20theoretical%20problems%20you%20think%20exist.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECloud%20security%20at%20the%20time%20was%20already%20a%20mature%20market.%20There%20were%20hundreds%20of%20solutions%20in%20the%20market.%20It's%20like%20when%20you%20go%20to%20a%20concert%2C%20the%20crowd%20is%20full%2C%20and%20you%20say%2C%20'I%20got%20here%20too%20late%2C%20there's%20no%20way%20I%20can%20get%20close%20to%20the%20stage.'%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20in%20reality%2C%20none%20of%20the%20solutions%20actually%20solved%20the%20real%20problem.%20The%20market%20existed%20to%20help%20customers%20securely%20manage%20the%20cloud%2C%20but%20what%20companies%20actually%20needed%20was%20security%20for%20everything%20they%20had%20%3Cem%3Ein%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20cloud.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20first%20year%2C%20we%20got%20to%20%2414%20million%20in%20annual%20recurring%20revenue%2C%20which%20was%2010%20times%20what%20we%20expected.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWiz%20grew%20as%20part%20of%20a%20mad%20dash%20of%20companies%20moving%20to%20the%20cloud.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Cstrong%3EHow%20does%20the%20disruption%20of%20the%20pandemic%20compare%20to%20what's%20happening%20now%20with%20artificial%20intelligence%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20remote%20first.%20We%20could%20hire%20any%20candidate%20we%20wanted.%20We%20could%20get%20any%20customer%20we%20wanted.%20This%20really%20helped%20us%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20the%20big%20companies%20had%20no%20advantage%20over%20us.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20pandemic%20accelerated%20stuff.%20AI%20changes%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20must%20forget%20everything%20we've%20done%20until%20now%20and%20approach%20security%20very%20differently.%20The%20reason%20is%20simple%3A%20Everyone%20can%20build%20very%20fast.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20talking%20a%20hundred%20times%20as%20fast%20as%20before.%20It's%20not%20just%20the%20number%20of%20applications%20increasing%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20the%20number%20of%20people%20in%20the%20company%20who%20can%20build%20stuff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20history%20of%20security%20in%20the%20enterprise%20was%20much%20more%20centralized.%20'You%20want%20to%20build%20something%3F%20Come%20to%20me.%20I%20will%20tell%20you%20what%20to%20do.'%20That's%20approaching%20it%20like%20a%20building%20inspector.%20In%20today's%20world%2C%20a%20builder%20can%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvibe-coding-tech-firms-hire-engineers-2025-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Evibe%20code%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20something%20in%20one%20hour.%20And%20there%20are%20hundreds%20of%20developers%20to%20every%20one%20security%20person.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20challenge%20for%20us%20is%20making%20security%20teams%20and%20developers%20work%20together%20when%20the%20business%20pushes%20them%20to%20move%20fast.%20Engineers%20clash%20with%20security.%20They%20say%2C%20'I%20don't%20have%20time%20for%20it.%20I'll%20deal%20with%20it%20later.'%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESecurity%20is%20mission-critical%20to%20a%20company%2C%20and%20yet%20it's%20seen%20as%20second-class%20within%20engineering.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20second-class%2C%20but%20it's%20also%20boring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20want%20to%20build%20an%20application%2C%20you%20think%20about%20how%20cool%20it%20will%20be.%20Are%20you%20thinking%20about%20security%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20say%20security%20has%20to%20be%20democratized%20%E2%80%94%20self-service.%20We%20simplify%20the%20complexity%20so%20anyone%20can%20own%20security.%20If%20you%20build%20it%2C%20you%20have%20to%20own%20it.%20It%20doesn't%20scale%20any%20other%20way.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20need%20to%20find%20a%20way%20as%20an%20industry%20to%20allow%20you%20to%20vibe%20code%2C%20but%20also%20vibe%20security%20while%20you%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20do%20you%20do%20that%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20to%20be%20designed%20so%20it's%20easy%20to%20use.%20The%20iPhone%20was%20nice%20to%20use%20%E2%80%94%20it%20wasn't%20just%20about%20the%20features.%20You%20have%20to%20enable%20anyone%20to%20use%20the%20features%20that%2C%20before%2C%20you%20needed%20to%20be%20an%20expert.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%20probably%20see%20some%20of%20the%20same%20challenges%20with%20hiring%E2%80%94%20pitching%20talent%20to%20do%20boring%2C%20but%20impactful%20work%3Cem%3E.%20%3C%2Fem%3EHow%20has%20your%20pitch%20to%20candidates%20evolved%20through%20the%20years%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20have%20to%20explain%20to%20technical%20people%20why%20cyber%20is%20cool.%20There's%20good%20and%20bad%2C%20and%20we%20are%20the%20people%20who%20find%20the%20problem%20before%20the%20bad%20guy%20comes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe're%20just%20five%20years%20old%2C%20although%20I%20admit%20there%20is%20a%20challenge%20around%20people%20saying%2C%20'you're%20not%20a%20startup%20anymore%3Cem%3E.'%3C%2Fem%3E%20I%20tell%20them%2C%20I'm%20forty-something%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%20You%20decide%20if%20you're%20young%20or%20not.%20I%20feel%20like%20we're%20still%20a%20startup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20are%20you%20hearing%20from%20customers%20lately%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20trying%20to%20cope%20with%20two%20different%20pressures.%20Some%20customers%20expect%20us%20to%20use%20AI%20to%20be%20smarter%2C%20and%20some%20are%20so%20afraid%20of%20the%20risks%20that%20they%20say%20in%20our%20contracts%2C%20'do%20not%20use%20it%20at%20all.'%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20a%20lot%20of%20discussions%20with%20customers.%20I%20try%20to%20tell%20them%20there's%20no%20way%20I%20can%20commit%20to%20that.%20There's%20a%20chance%20a%20support%20email%20will%20come%2C%20and%20a%20summary%20will%20run.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20a%20highly%20regulated%20entity%2C%20but%20we%20are%20also%20expected%20to%20run%20very%20fast.%20The%20challenge%20is%3A%20how%20can%20we%20leverage%20AI%20internally%20without%20putting%20data%20or%20customers%20at%20risk%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI've%20read%20about%20how%20much%20code%20AI%20writes%20at%20Google%20or%20Microsoft%2C%20and%20it%20seems%20like%20showboating.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20don't%20know%20the%20real%20impact%20on%20productivity%20yet%2C%20that's%20the%20truth.%20The%20amount%20of%20code%20being%20generated%20doesn't%20really%20mean%20that%20you%20can%20take%20away%20strong%20engineers%20from%20complex%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20starting%20to%20build%20different%20pipelines%3A%20an%20internal%20flow%20for%20employees%20and